    <h1>Check Scratch For Purge</h1>
    <p>This tool allows you to view which files will be purged from <code>/scratch</code>. You can also download a list of the filenames to be purged locally or save it to your home or scratch directories.</p>
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
      <div class="buttons">
        <button class="btn btn-primary m-2" onclick="toggleOutput()">Show Files to be Purged</button>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary m-2" id="downloadHome" href="#">Save Filenames to Home Directory</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary m-2" id="downloadScratch" href="#">Save Filenames to Scratch Directory</a>
        <button class="btn btn-secondary m-2" onclick="downloadLocally()">Download Filenames Locally</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="output" class="mt-4" style="display: none;">
      <h2>Files to be Purged</h2>
      <p>The following <%= @output.size %> files will be purged:</p>
      <ul>
        <div id="fileList">
          <% @output.each do |line| %>
          <li><%= line %></li>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
  <footer class="footer mt-4">
    <h2>Scratch Purging Policy</h2>
    <p>For more information on the policy for removing files in scratch after 90 days, please visit the <a href="https://www.rc.virginia.edu/2024/07/reinstatement-of-file-purging-of-personal-/scratch-files-on-afton-and-rivanna/" target="_blank">File Purging Policy</a> page.</p>
  </footer>
